tissueExpression.summary: Cells in seminiferus ducts, placental trophoblasts, renal tubules, thyroid and adrenal glands showed strong cytoplasmic immunoreactivity. Lymphoid tissues, male genitalia tract, myocytes, neuropil and subsets of cells in the CNS showed moderate to strong cytoplasmic positivity. Hepatocytes and ductal cells in salivary gland showed strong membranous positivity. Remaining normal tissues were in general weakly stained or negative. Detected at High or Medium expression level in 26 of 81 analyzed normal tissue cell types.

subcellularLocation.summary: Mainly localized to the nuclear membrane. In addition localized to the cytoplasm & centrosome.

tissueExpression.summary: Most hepatocellular carcinomas and non-Hodgkins lymphomas along with a few malignant melanomas, breast, testicular, pancreatic and renal cancers displayed moderate to strong cytoplasmic immunoreactivity. Remaining malignant cells were weakly stained or negative.
